 with various ways of being in the presence of God. The Greek tradition allows for a greater degree of unification and participation in the divine. The New Testament texts are generally closer to the Greek tradition, although Greek philosophy would have a huge effect on later Christian mysticism.The book is intended for scholars and advanced students of ancient Judaism and early Christianity.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 4aApokalyptik. 4aMystik. 4aPhilon von Alexandria. 4aQumranschriften. 7aRELIGION / Biblical Criticism & Interpretation / New Testament.2bisacsh  aApokalypticism.  aDead Sea Scrolls.  aMysticism.  aPhilo.1 aCollins, Adela Yarbro, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCollins, John J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCollins, John J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDecock, Paul B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrey, Jörg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLevison, Jack, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSterling, Gregory E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVilliers, Pieter G. R., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aYarbro Collins, Adela, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 ade Villiers, Pieter G.R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2018 Part 1z978311076248808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2018z978311071955008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishz978311060425208iTitle is part of eBook packa